claim.claim-text:
23. A method of generating a digital image with an image detector, comprising:
generating a plurality of signals, by a digital image sensor of the image detector, in response to x--rays incident on the sensor;
generating a digital representation of an x-ray image, by a first processor of the image detector that is in a first active state, based on the plurality of signals;
causing, in response to generating a plurality of signals, a second processor that is in a second idle state to enter a second active state by transmitting a wake signal to the second processor from the first processor; and
transmitting the digital representation to the second processor while the second processor is in the second active state.
